---
// StorageScale.astro — "the claim, drawn to scale".
// Replaces the old stats band + abstract flow diagram. Instead of telling
// the visitor numbers, it draws what ten uploads of the same artifact do
// to a bucket: full copies on the left, one reference + hairline deltas on
// the right. The figures are the verified 61,400%-smaller datapoint family
// used site-wide (91 MB artifact → 148 KB delta), and the v100 projection
// lands on the real 8,850%-smaller catalog number from the migration log —
// on purpose.
const VERSIONS = 10;
const rows = Array.from({ length: VERSIONS }, (_, i) => i + 1);
---

<section class="section scale">
  <div class="shell">
    <span class="section-eyebrow">Drawn to scale</span>
    <h2 class="scale-title">What ten releases do to a bucket</h2>
    <p class="scale-sub">
      The same ten uploads of a 91&nbsp;MB build artifact, stored two ways.
      The bars are proportional — we had to give the deltas a two-pixel
      floor so you could see them at all.
    </p>

    <div
      class="scale-chart"
      role="img"
      aria-label="Bar chart comparing ten versions of a 91 megabyte artifact. In a plain S3 bucket every version is a full 91 megabyte copy, totalling 910 megabytes. Behind DeltaGlider, version one is a full 91 megabyte reference and versions two through ten are 148 kilobyte deltas, totalling 92.3 megabytes."
    >
      <div class="scale-row scale-head-row" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="vlabel"></span>
        <span class="scale-head">Plain S3 bucket</span>
        <span class="scale-head scale-head-b">Behind DeltaGlider</span>
      </div>

      {rows.map((v) => (
        <div class="scale-row" style={`--i:${v}`} aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="vlabel">v{v}</span>
          <span class="track">
            <i class="fill fill-a">{v === 1 ? '91 MB' : ''}</i>
          </span>
          <span class="track">
            {v === 1 ? (
              <i class="fill fill-ref">91 MB · reference</i>
            ) : (
              <>
                <i class="fill fill-d"></i>
                {v === 2 && <span class="d-label">148 KB</span>}
              </>
            )}
          </span>
        </div>
      ))}

      <div class="scale-row scale-more" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="vlabel">⋮</span>
        <span class="more-text">every further version: +91 MB</span>
        <span class="more-text more-text-b">+148 KB</span>
      </div>

      <div class="scale-row scale-totals" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="vlabel"></span>
        <span class="total total-a">910 MB <em>billed</em></span>
        <span class="total total-b">92.3 MB <em>billed</em></span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="scale-projection">
      The gap widens with every release. By v100 it's <strong>9.1&nbsp;GB</strong>
      against <strong>~106&nbsp;MB</strong> — 8,600% less. Our own release catalog
      landed at <a href="/case-studies/readonlyrest-builds">8,850% smaller on a
      real release line</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="scale-mech">
      The mechanism, in one sentence: each upload is stored as a binary
      diff against a full reference copy kept beside it, and every read
      rebuilds the exact original — behind the same S3 API your tools
      already speak.
    </p>

    <aside class="scale-objection">
      <p class="objection-q">
        “Our artifacts are ZIPs and JARs. They're already compressed —
        diffing them should do nothing.”
      </p>
      <p class="objection-a">
        It would, on random bytes. But versioned archives aren't random:
        version to version, the same entries land in the same order — same
        manifest, same icons, same bundled CSS — so the binary diff stays
        tiny. The 91&nbsp;MB artifact in the chart <em>is</em> a compressed
        ZIP — a real ReadonlyREST plugin, stored 61,400% smaller.
        <a href="/docs/explanation/delta-compression">The engineering
        note</a> walks through why.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .scale-title { margin-top: 0; }

  .scale-sub {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin: 0 0 2.25rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .scale-chart {
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 2.25rem 2.5rem 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  .scale-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3.2rem 1fr 1fr;
    column-gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .scale-head-row { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }

  .scale-head {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .scale-head-b { color: var(--brand-dark); }

  .vlabel {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    text-align: right;
    padding-right: 0.2rem;
  }

  .track {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    height: 34px;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .fill {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding-inline: 12px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-style: normal;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    transform-origin: left center;
    animation: scale-grow 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1) both;
    animation-delay: calc(var(--i, 0) * 55ms);
  }

  .fill-a {
    width: 100%;
    background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.22);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .fill-ref {
    width: 100%;
    background: rgba(217, 70, 239, 0.16);
    border: 1px solid rgba(217, 70, 239, 0.45);
    color: #f0abfc;
  }

  /* 148 KB / 91 MB = 0.163% — the 3px floor is the only generosity */
  .fill-d {
    width: max(3px, 0.163%);
    padding: 0;
    background: var(--brand);
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.7);
  }

  .d-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    margin-left: 0.7rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .scale-more {
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
  }
  .more-text {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .more-text-b { color: var(--brand-dark); }

  .scale-totals {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    padding-top: 1.3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .total {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 2.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ink-strong);
  }
  .total em {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }
  .total-b {
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    text-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.45);
  }

  .scale-projection {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0;
    color: var(--ink-strong);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }

  .scale-mech {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .scale-objection {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0;
    padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--brand);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  .objection-q {
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink-strong);
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .objection-a {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: none;
  }

  @keyframes scale-grow {
    from { transform: scaleX(0); opacity: 0; }
    to   { transform: scaleX(1); opacity: 1; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .scale-chart { padding: 1.25rem 1rem 1.1rem; }
    .scale-row { column-gap: 0.8rem; grid-template-columns: 2.2rem 1fr 1fr; }
    .scale-head { font-size: 0.7rem; }
    .vlabel { font-size: 0.72rem; }
    .track { height: 24px; }
    .fill { font-size: 0.66rem; padding-inline: 6px; }
    .d-label { font-size: 0.68rem; }
    .more-text { font-size: 0.62rem; }
    .total { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    .total em { display: block; margin: 0.1rem 0 0; }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .fill { animation: none !important; }
  }
</style>
